new app area
Structure:

User (personal identity)
→ belongs to Company (commercial identity)
→ Company holds Subscription
→ Company owns Campaigns
→ Campaign owns Pitches
→ Pitches spawn Negotiations / Messages

This avoids every future permission conflict.

Bare-bones IA for phase 1 (the app area as the spine):
	1.	Dashboard (home screen)
Functions:

	•	Discover new campaigns (algorithmic + category filter)
	•	See active negotiations
	•	See drafts / in-progress campaigns
	•	Quick actions: New Campaign, New Pitch

This is the “command centre”.
	2.	Campaigns
Company-level list

	•	Active
	•	Draft
	•	Closed
Campaign detail must show inbound pitches, status, and controls.

	3.	Pitches
Your outgoing and incoming combined view, filtered by:

	•	Sent
	•	Received
	•	Needs reply
	•	Accepted
	•	Declined

	4.	Messages / Negotiations
Threaded inbox with right-hand AI query panel.
Each thread tied to a pitch.
Declining closes thread.
	5.	Profile and Company Settings
User: name, email, photo.
Company: logo, URL, vertical, subscription status, billing.



